# Variable Naming

Prefer readable, self-documenting variable names. Avoid cryptic abbreviations or single-letter names outside of trivial loop indices.

```python
# Bad
has_area = self.forecast_area_id is not None
has_coords = self.latitude is not None

# Good
has_forecast_area = self.forecast_area_id is not None
has_coordinates = self.latitude is not None
```

When naming boolean flags, prefix with `has_`, `is_`, or `should_` and spell out the full concept being tested.
